<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,537,2041]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,645,672]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Integument papillae strongly elongated and distally narrowed (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1139,646,673]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1935,1960]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,234,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,229,1915]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 11. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–d. H. lasioderma female (MD 120a); a. integument structure; b. III-L-5–6; c. IV-L-5–6; d. Cx-I+II; e.–h. H. mesembrina male (MD 151); e. coxal and genital field; f. integument papillae; g. III-L-4–6; h. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613324/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 11 a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1152,1228,646,673]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1330,1355]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,174,1310]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,174,1310]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 12. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–e. H. lasioderma (MD 154b); a.–b. female and male Cx-I+II; c.–e. integument papillae in various views; f.–i. H. mesembrina (MD 151); f. female Cx-I+II; g.–i. integument papillae in various views; k.–n. H. zhokhovi female; k. Cx-I+II; l.–n. integument papillae in various views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613326" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613326/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
12 c 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1199,1213,646,672]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">–</emphasis>
e
</figureCitation>
). Posterior margin of Cx-IV with posterolateral apodeme relatively long and strong, directed medially. Swimming setae (anterior/posterior) II-L-5, 0/1; III-L-4, 0/2; III-L-5, 0/2-3; IV-L-4, 0-1/3; IV-L-5, 0/3. Leg claw length (all legs) 45 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1296,1310,718,744]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">–</emphasis>
65 – 17 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1394,1408,718,744]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">–</emphasis>
23 % L penultimate segment. Leg segments relatively stout (e.g., L/H ratio I-L-5, 4.0 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1099,1113,754,780]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">–</emphasis>
4.3; II-L-5, 4.2 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1285,1299,754,780]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">–</emphasis>
5.0; III-L-5, 4.8 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[186,200,790,816]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">–</emphasis>
5.2; IV-L-5, 5.4 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[376,390,790,816]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">–</emphasis>
5.9–see 
<figureCitation box="[481,610,790,817]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1935,1960]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,234,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,229,1915]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 11. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–d. H. lasioderma female (MD 120a); a. integument structure; b. III-L-5–6; c. IV-L-5–6; d. Cx-I+II; e.–h. H. mesembrina male (MD 151); e. coxal and genital field; f. integument papillae; g. III-L-4–6; h. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613324/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
Fig. 11 b 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[581,595,790,816]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">–</emphasis>
c
