<figureCitation box="[780,886,898,924]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1935,1960]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,234,1914]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,229,1915]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 11. Family Hydrodromidae, genus Hydrodroma. a.–d. H. lasioderma female (MD 120a); a. integument structure; b. III-L-5–6; c. IV-L-5–6; d. Cx-I+II; e.–h. H. mesembrina male (MD 151); e. coxal and genital field; f. integument papillae; g. III-L-4–6; h. IV-L-4–6." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3613324" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3613324/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Figs 11 d</figureCitation>
