<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1472,1608]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,1472,1499]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Distribution:</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus box="[613,661,1474,1500]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
locality in Montagne d’Ambre at the northern end of 
<collectingCountry box="[1271,1408,1473,1499]" name="Madagascar" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. It can be considered a Northern sister species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gerecke" authorityYear="2020" box="[671,826,1509,1535]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydrodromidae" genus="Hydrodroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="megalonyx">
<emphasis box="[671,826,1509,1535]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">H. megalonyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the S and W of the island.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1472,1608]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,1544,1571]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Habitat:</emphasis>
Probably a rhithrobiont, as suggested by the reduced number of swimming setae. The 
<typeStatus box="[1271,1319,1546,1572]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
locality is a low order stream with few pool areas; no standing waters exist in the surroundings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
